-- Emerging-Market Bond, Equity Fund Inflows Head for Record Year, EPFR Says
-- B y   G a r f i e l d   R e y n o l d s
-- 2010-10-01T02:52:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-01/emerging-market-bond-equity-fund-inflows-head-for-record-year-epfr-says.html
(Corrects to show equity funds received $30.2 billion in
second paragraph.)  Funds investing in the equities of
emerging markets are heading for a record year of inflows, as
are funds covering emerging-market bonds, EPFR Global said in an
e-mailed statement.  Investors put a net $30.2 billion into emerging-market
equity funds in the three months ended Sept. 30, while putting
$15.2 billion into emerging-market bonds, EPFR said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
